+# ADS131M08 patched driver notes
+
+This package contains a patched version of the original driver focused on stability and streaming reliability on Raspberry Pi CM5 / Raspberry Pi OS Bookworm.
+
+## Main changes
+
+- Removed unsafe shared `spin_lock_irqsave()` flag storage from the custom list and chunk buffer code.
+- Switched DRDY/RST handling from hard-coded global GPIO numbers to descriptor-based GPIOs (`drdy-gpios`, `reset-gpios`) taken from Device Tree.
+- Fixed the blocking read path to wait on the actual ready-queue state instead of a global condition flag.
+- Made the char device single-open logic race-safe with `atomic_cmpxchg()`.
+- Blocked destructive SPI control ioctls while continuous sampling is running to avoid protocol collisions.
+- Added SPI transfer serialization with a mutex.
+- Fixed SPI error paths so transfer buffers are always returned.
+- Increased the number of chunk buffers from 3 to 8 to reduce overrun pressure.
+- When no chunk buffer is available, the IRQ thread now performs a discard read to keep the ADC/SPI frame stream aligned and increments a drop counter.
+- Added drop counter visibility to `/proc/ads131m08`.
+- `RESET` now clocks a full-length frame instead of an undersized one.
+- Probe/remove cleanup paths were tightened up and now call `ads131m08_spi_exit()`.
+- The driver now respects the SPI speed supplied by Device Tree unless it is absent.
+
+## Device Tree expectation
+
+The driver now expects these DT properties on the SPI device node:
+
+- `drdy-gpios`
+- `reset-gpios`
+
+Example values are already added to the provided DTS overlay files.
+
+## Notes
+
+- The package is source-only; previous build artifacts were removed from the release tarball.
+- I did not add DMA in this revision.
+- I also did not redesign the driver around `spi_async()` yet; this patch keeps the current synchronous data path but removes the most obvious correctness issues first.
+
+## Build sanity check
+
+- Compiled successfully in the container against Linux 6.12.69 headers as a syntax/API sanity check.
+- Target runtime remains Raspberry Pi CM5 / 6.6.51, so you should still rebuild on-target or against the exact Pi kernel headers.
